lender.name: Peter
lender.loan_because: I loan because I want to empower impoverished rural dwellers especially women and girls such that they are able to take care of their own destiny and improve their environment as a means of poverty alleviation and raising their self esteem.
lender.occupational_info: Our work is involved with working in rural communities of Liberia to help rural poor women and girls especially following the cessation of 14 years of civil crisis in Liberia. The war created a gap level amongst the citizenry and those affected the most are women and youth in general especially so, there was practically no learning opportunity in rural Liberia. This means young people grew without the opportunity of going to school to learn. Besides, over forty percent of the Liberian population is youth based suggesting this group of people needs to be cater to by offering them livelihood skills that will create a means for sustainability. Besides, opportunity in rural communities are wanting and those in dire need are the women, who serve as bread winners for the family and doing all the odd jobs to ensure their families are taken care of. In line with these circumstances, we are soliciting opportunities to cater to the social welfare of rural women and empower them to become self sufficient. Against this background, we are trusting that our programs - rural girls education, micro credit for empowerment of women, skills development for youth and advocacy against gender based violence will be supported to help fill in the gap.
